  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Constructing Meshes"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "To create a 3D object, create a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in Euclid.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "You can manually create an array of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Polygon",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instances, but that’s pretty tedious.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Euclid offers a number of helper methods to quickly create complex geometry.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Primitive-Geometry",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Primitive Geometry",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The simplest way to create a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " is to start with an existing primitive, such as a cube or sphere.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The following primitive types are available in Euclid, and are defined as static constructor methods on ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/cube(center:size:faces:wrapMode:material:)-8t5q8",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - A cubic ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " (or cuboid, if you specify different values for the width, height and\/or depth).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/sphere(radius:slices:stacks:poleDetail:faces:wrapMode:material:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - A spherical ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/cylinder(radius:height:slices:poleDetail:faces:wrapMode:material:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - A cylindrical ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/cone(radius:height:slices:stacks:poleDetail:addDetailAtBottomPole:faces:wrapMode:material:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " -  A conical ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "All ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instances are made of flat polygons.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Since true curves cannot be represented using straight edges, the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "sphere",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "cylinder",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "cone",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " primitives are approximations.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Control the quality of these approximations by using the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "slices",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and\/or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "stacks",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " parameters to configure the level of detail.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In addition to the 3D ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " primitives listed, there are also 2D ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " primitives.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "These are implemented as static constructor methods on the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " type instead of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Path\/line(_:color:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - A straight line.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Path\/ellipse(width:height:segments:color:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "- A closed, elliptical ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Path\/circle(radius:segments:color:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "  - A closed, circular ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Path\/rectangle(width:height:color:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - A closed, rectangular ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Path\/roundedRectangle(width:height:radius:detail:color:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - A closed, rectangular ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " with rounded corners.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Path\/square(size:color:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - Same as ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path\/rectangle(width:height:color:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ", but with equal width and height.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Path\/polygon(radius:sides:color:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - A regular polygon shape (not to be confused with Euclid’s ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Polygon",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " type).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Builders",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Builders",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Geometric primitives are all very well, but there is a limit to what you can create by combining spheres, cubes, etc.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "As an intermediate step between the extremes of using predefined primitives or individually positioning polygons, you can use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "builders",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Builders create a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " from a (typically) 2D ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The following builders are defined as static constructor functions on the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " type:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/fill(_:faces:material:isCancelled:)-(Path,_,_,_)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - This builder fills a single ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " to create a pair of ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Polygon",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "s (front and back faces).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/stroke(_:width:detail:material:isCancelled:)-85o14",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - This builder strokes a single ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " to create a strip or tube. A second variant (",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/stroke(_:width:detail:material:isCancelled:)-(Collection<LineSegment>,_,_,_,_)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ") of the function accepts an collection of ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "LineSegment",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ", which is convenient for creating a wireframe geometry from the ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "uniqueEdges",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " of a ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/lathe(_:slices:poleDetail:addDetailForFlatPoles:faces:wrapMode:material:isCancelled:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - This builder takes a 2D ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " and rotates it around the Y-axis to create a rotationally symmetrical ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ". This is an easy way to create complex shapes like candlesticks, chess pieces, rocket ships, etc.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/extrude(_:along:twist:align:faces:material:isCancelled:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - This builder fills a ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " and extrudes it along its axis, or another path. This can turn a circular path into a tube, or a square into a cube etc.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/loft(_:faces:material:isCancelled:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - This builder is similar to ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/extrude(_:along:twist:align:faces:material:isCancelled:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ", but takes multiple ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " instances and joins them. The sequence of ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " instances do not need to be the same shape, but must all have the same number of points and subpaths. To work correctly, each ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " must be pre-positioned in 3D space so they do not all lie on the same plane.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/convexHull(of:material:isCancelled:)-(Collection<Vector>,_,_)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - Similar the the ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/loft(_:faces:material:isCancelled:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " builder, this method can form a Mesh by wrapping a skin around one or more ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Path",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " instances. But unlike the other builders, in addition to paths you can also form a convex hull around a collection of meshes, polygons, vertices or points.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Curves",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Curves",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Builders are a powerful tool for creating interesting ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instances from one or more ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instances, but what about creating an interesting ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in the first place?",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Creating a polygonal ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " by specifying points individually is straightforward, but creating ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "curves",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " that way is tedious.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "That’s where ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Bezier",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " curves come in. Beziers allow you to specify complex curves using just a few control points.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Euclid exposes this feature via the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path\/curve(_:detail:)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " constructor method.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path\/curve(_:detail:)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " method takes an array of ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "PathPoint",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "detail",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " argument.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Normally, the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "PathPoint\/isCurved",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " property is used to calculate surface normals (for lighting purposes), but with the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path\/curve(_:detail:)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " method it actually affects the shape of the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A sequence of regular (non-curved) ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "PathPoint",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "s create sharp corners in the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " as normal, but curved ones are treated as off-curve Bezier control points.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "detail",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " argument of the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path\/curve(_:detail:)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " method controls how many line segments are used to approximate the curve.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path\/curve(_:detail:)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " method uses second-order (quadratic) Bezier curves, where each curve has two on-curve end points and a single off-curve control point.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "If two curved ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "PathPoint",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " are used in sequence then an on-curve point is interpolated between them.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "It is therefore  possible to create curves entirely out of curved (off-curve) control points.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This approach to curve generation is based on the popular ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/fonts\/TrueType-Reference-Manual\/RM01\/Chap1.html",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", and provides a good balance between simplicity and flexibility.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For more complex curves, on macOS and iOS you can create Euclid ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " from a Core Graphics ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "CGPath",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " by using the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "CGPath.paths()",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " extension method.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "CGPath",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " supports cubic bezier curves as well as quadratic.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Constructive-Solid-Geometry-CSG",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Constructive Solid Geometry (CSG)",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "CSG is another powerful tool for creating intricate geometry.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "CSG allows you to perform boolean operations (logical AND, OR, etc.) on solid shapes.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The following CSG operations are defined as methods on the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " type:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/subtracting(_:isCancelled:)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - Subtracts the volume of one ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " from another.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/symmetricDifference(_:isCancelled:)-swift.type.method",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - Produces a shape representing the non-overlapping parts of the input ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "es (this is useful for rendering text glyphs).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/union(_:isCancelled:)-swift.method",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - Combines two intersecting ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "es, removing internal faces and leaving only the outer shell around both shapes (logical OR).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/intersection(_:isCancelled:)-swift.method",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - Returns a single ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " representing the common volume of two intersecting ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "es (logical AND).",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/stencil(_:isCancelled:)-swift.method",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - This effectively “paints” part of one ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " with the material from another.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/convexHull(with:isCancelled:)-swift.method",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - This creates a convex hull around one or more meshes.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "Mesh\/minkowskiSum(with:isCancelled:)-(Mesh,_)",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " - This traces the edges of one mesh with another.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Most CSG operations require ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "es that are “watertight”, that is they have no holes in their surface.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Using a CSG operation on a mesh that isn’t sealed may result in unexpected results.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Text",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Text",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "On macOS and iOS you can make use of Euclid’s Core Text integration to create 2D or 3D extruded text.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path\/text(_:width:detail:)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " method produces an array of 2D ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " that represent the contours of each glyph in an ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "AttributedString",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". You can use these paths with either ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh\/fill(_:faces:material:isCancelled:)-([Path],_,_,_)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh\/extrude(_:depth:twist:sections:faces:material:isCancelled:)-(Collection<Path>,_,_,_,_,_,_)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " builder methods to create solid text.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Alternatively, the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Mesh\/text(_:font:width:depth:detail:material:)",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " constructor directly produces an extruded 3D text model from a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "String",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "AttributedString",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Each glyph in the input string maps to a single ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " in the result, but these ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "s may contain nested subpaths.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Glyphs formed from multiple subpaths will be filled using the even-odd rule (equivalent to using ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "symmetricDifference",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " with the individually filled or extruded subpaths).",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
